{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884441972,"sessionID":"ses_2850a6bffffeycy4lHOS3Q6Or6","part":{"id":"prt_d7af619100013nmBPeGF34YCLf","messageID":"msg_d7af603f0001DtkyEAUNhgkWqA","sessionID":"ses_2850a6bffffeycy4lHOS3Q6Or6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6aa4bcf0c7e745cba5235145d24f9d14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: **Module:** `manifests`  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a Helm Chart metadata file with correct API version and component information.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure\n22: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` is created\n23: - **WHEN** the file is written\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n25:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n26:   - `name: agentcube`\n27:   - `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n28:   - `version: 0.1.0` (chart version)\n29:   - `appVersion: 1.0.0` (application version)\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Chart dependencies\n32: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml defines optional subchart dependencies\n33: - **WHEN** external charts are needed\n34: - **THEN** dependencies SHALL be listed in `dependencies` array with `name`, `version`, `repository`, and optional `condition` for enabling/disabling\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ### Requirement: values.yaml default configuration\n39: \n40: The system SHALL provide comprehensive default values for all deployable components.\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Global values section\n43: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` is created\n44: - **WHEN** global configuration is defined\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n46:   - `imagePullSecrets: []` (array of secret names for private registries)\n47:   - `nameOverride: \"\"` (partial name override)\n48:   - `fullnameOverride: \"\"` (full name override)\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Redis connection values\n51: - **GIVEN** redis configuration is needed for router and workloadmanager\n52: - **WHEN** values.yaml defines redis settings\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n54:   - `redis.addr: \"\"` (Redis address, format `host:port`)\n55:   - `redis.password: \"\"` (Redis password, empty for no auth)\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Router deployment values\n58: - **GIVEN** router component is configurable\n59: - **WHEN** values.yaml defines router section\n60: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n61:   - `router.replicas: 1` (int)\n62:   - `router.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` (string)\n63:   - `router.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (string)\n64:   - `router.image.tag: latest` (string)\n65:   - `router.service.type: ClusterIP` (string)\n66:   - `router.service.port: 8080` (int)\n67:   - `router.service.targetPort: 8080` (int)\n68:   - `router.resources.limits.cpu: 500m` (string)\n69:   - `router.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi` (string)\n70:   - `router.resources.requests.cpu: 100m` (string)\n71:   - `router.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi` (string)\n72:   - `router.config: {}` (object)\n73:   - `router.extraEnv: []` (array)\n74:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` (string)\n75:   - `router.rbac.create: false` (bool)\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager deployment values\n78: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager component is configurable\n79: - **WHEN** values.yaml defines workloadmanager section\n80: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n81:   - `workloadmanager.replicas: 1` (int)\n82:   - `workloadmanager.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` (string)\n83:   - `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (string)\n84:   - `workloadmanager.image.tag: latest` (string)\n85:   - `workloadmanager.service.type: ClusterIP` (string)\n86:   - `workloadmanager.service.port: 8080` (int)\n87:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 500m` (string)\n88:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi` (string)\n89:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu: 100m` (string)\n90:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi` (string)\n91:   - `workloadmanager.extraEnv: []` (array)\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler optional values\n94: - **GIVEN** volcano scheduler is an optional component\n95: - **WHEN** values.yaml defines volcano.scheduler section\n96: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n97:   - `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (bool, disabled by default)\n98:   - `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 1` (int)\n99:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` (string)\n100:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (string)\n101:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.tag: latest` (string)\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: WorkloadManager Deployment template\n106: \n107: The system SHALL template WorkloadManager Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources, and environment.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Deployment metadata\n110: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n111: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n112: - **THEN** Deployment metadata SHALL include:\n113:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n114:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n115:   - `labels` using helper templates\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Deployment spec replicas\n118: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager Deployment is templated\n119: - **WHEN** replicas value is specified\n120: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Deployment container image\n123: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager container is defined\n124: - **WHEN** image values are set\n125: - **THEN** container image SHALL be:\n126:   - `image: \"{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\"`\n127:   - `imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}`\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Deployment environment variables\n130: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager needs namespace and redis config\n131: - **WHEN** env section is templated\n132: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n133:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from `fieldRef: metadata.namespace`\n134:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values\n135:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from values\n136:   - Extra env from `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.extraEnv }}`\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Deployment container args\n139: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager needs port configuration\n140: - **WHEN** args are templated\n141: - **THEN** args SHALL include:\n142:   - `--port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n143:   - `--runtime-class-name=` (empty string for default)\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Deployment resources\n146: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager has configurable resources\n147: - **WHEN** resources section is templated\n148: - **THEN** `resources` SHALL map from `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.resources }}`\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: Deployment health probes\n151: - **GIVEN** workloadmanager needs health endpoints\n152: - **WHEN** liveness and readiness probes are defined\n153: - **THEN** both SHALL be HTTP GET:\n154:   - `path: /health`\n155:   - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n156:   - liveness: `initialDelaySeconds: 10`, `periodSeconds: 10`\n157:   - readiness: `initialDelaySeconds: 5`, `periodSeconds: 5`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Deployment imagePullSecrets optional\n160: - **GIVEN** `imagePullSecrets` array in global values\n161: - **WHEN** array is non-empty\n162: - **THEN** `spec.template.spec.imagePullSecrets` SHALL be rendered from values\n163: - **WHEN** array is empty\n164: - **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` section SHALL be omitted\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: WorkloadManager Service template\n169: \n170: The system SHALL template WorkloadManager Service with configurable type and port.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Service metadata\n173: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager Service is rendered\n174: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n175: - **THEN** Service SHALL have:\n176:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n177:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n178:   - `labels` matching Deployment\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Service spec\n181: - **GIVEN** Service is templated\n182: - **WHEN** service values are defined\n183: - **THEN** Service spec SHALL include:\n184:   - `type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}`\n185:   - `ports` array with:\n186:     - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n187:     - `targetPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n188:     - `protocol: TCP`\n189:     - `name: http`\n190:   - `selector: app: workloadmanager`\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ### Requirement: Router Deployment template\n195: \n196: The system SHALL template Router Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources, and environment including Redis and WorkloadManager URLs.\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Router Deployment metadata\n199: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` is rendered\n200: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n201: - **THEN** Deployment SHALL have:\n202:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n203:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n204:   - `labels` using helper templates\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Router Deployment replicas\n207: - **GIVEN** router Deployment is templated\n208: - **WHEN** replicas value is specified\n209: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.replicas }}`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName conditional\n212: - **GIVEN** router Deployment needs optional service account\n213: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is non-empty\n214: - **THEN** `spec.template.spec.serviceAccountName` SHALL be set to that value\n215: - **WHEN** value is empty\n216: - **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL be omitted (uses default)\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Router container image\n219: - **GIVEN** router container is defined\n220: - **WHEN** image values are set\n221: - **THEN** container image SHALL be:\n222:   - `image: \"{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\"`\n223:   - `imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}`\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Router container port\n226: - **GIVEN** router exposes HTTP port\n227: - **WHEN** container ports are defined\n228: - **THEN** `ports` SHALL include:\n229:   - `containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n230:   - `protocol: TCP`\n231:   - `name: http`\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Router environment variables\n234: - **GIVEN** router needs namespace, redis, and workloadmanager config\n235: - **WHEN** env section is templated\n236: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n237:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from `fieldRef: metadata.namespace`\n238:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from values\n239:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values\n240:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n241:   - Extra env from `{{ .Values.router.extraEnv }}`\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Router container args\n244: - **GIVEN** router needs port and debug configuration\n245: - **WHEN** args are templated\n246: - **THEN** args SHALL include:\n247:   - `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n248:   - `--debug`\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: Router resources\n251: - **GIVEN** router has configurable resources\n252: - **WHEN** resources section is templated\n253: - **THEN** `resources` SHALL map from `{{ .Values.router.resources }}`\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Router health probes\n256: - **GIVEN** router needs separate liveness and readiness endpoints\n257: - **WHEN** probes are defined\n258: - **THEN** probes SHALL be HTTP GET on `{{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`:\n259:   - liveness: `path: /health/live`, `initialDelaySeconds: 1`, `periodSeconds: 2`\n260:   - readiness: `path: /health/ready`, `initialDelaySeconds: 1`, `periodSeconds: 2`\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ### Requirement: Router Service template\n265: \n266: The system SHALL template Router Service with configurable type, port, and targetPort.\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Router Service metadata\n269: - **GIVEN** Router Service is rendered\n270: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n271: - **THEN** Service SHALL have:\n272:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n273:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n274:   - `labels` matching Deployment\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Router Service spec\n277: - **GIVEN** Service is templated\n278: - **WHEN** service values are defined\n279: - **THEN** Service spec SHALL include:\n280:   - `type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}`\n281:   - `ports` array with:\n282:     - `port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}`\n283:     - `targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n284:     - `protocol: TCP`\n285:     - `name: http`\n286:   - `selector: app: agentcube-router`\n287: \n288: ---\n289: \n290: ### Requirement: WorkloadManager RBAC template\n291: \n292: The system SHALL template WorkloadManager RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding).\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager\n295: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n296: - **WHEN** helm template executes\n297: - **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n298:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n299:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: ClusterRole for WorkloadManager\n302: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs cluster-scoped permissions\n303: - **WHEN** ClusterRole is templated\n304: - **THEN** ClusterRole `workloadmanager` SHALL have rules:\n305: \n306: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n307: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n308: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n309: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n310: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n311: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n312: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n313: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n314: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n315: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n316: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n317: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n318: | `\"\"` (core) | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n319: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n320: | `\"\"` (core) | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: ClusterRoleBinding for WorkloadManager\n323: - **GIVEN** WorkloadManager ClusterRole needs binding\n324: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is templated\n325: - **THEN** ClusterRoleBinding `workloadmanager` SHALL have:\n326:   - `subjects`: ServiceAccount `workloadmanager` in `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n327:   - `roleRef`: ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n328: \n329: ---\n330: \n331: ### Requirement: Router RBAC template (conditional)\n332: \n333: The system SHALL conditionally template Router RBAC resources when `router.rbac.create` is true.\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Router RBAC conditional rendering\n336: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` exists\n337: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.rbac.create }}` is `true`\n338: - **THEN** ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding SHALL be rendered\n339: - **WHEN** value is `false`\n340: - **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be rendered for router\n341: \n342: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount name derivation\n343: - **GIVEN** router RBAC is enabled\n344: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is non-empty\n345: - **THEN** ServiceAccount name SHALL be that value\n346: - **WHEN** value is empty\n347: - **THEN** ServiceAccount name SHALL default to `agentcube-router`\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: Router Role permissions\n350: - **GIVEN** router needs namespace-scoped secret access\n351: - **WHEN** Role is templated\n352: - **THEN** Role SHALL have rules:\n353:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n354:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n355:   - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding\n358: - **GIVEN** router Role needs binding\n359: - **WHEN** RoleBinding is templated\n360: - **THEN** RoleBinding SHALL reference:\n361:   - `subjects`: ServiceAccount with derived name in release namespace\n362:   - `roleRef`: Role with same name\n363: \n364: ---\n365: \n366: ### Requirement: Volcano Agent Scheduler template (conditional)\n367: \n368: The system SHALL conditionally template Volcano Agent Scheduler when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n369: \n370: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler conditional rendering\n371: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` exists\n372: - **WHEN** `{{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}` is `true`\n373: - **THEN** all scheduler resources SHALL be rendered\n374: - **WHEN** value is `false`\n375: - **THEN** no scheduler resources SHALL be rendered\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler ServiceAccount\n378: - **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n379: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is templated\n380: - **THEN** `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler ConfigMap\n383: - **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n384: - **WHEN** ConfigMap is templated\n385: - **THEN** ConfigMap `volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` SHALL have:\n386:   - `data.agent-scheduler.conf` containing scheduler configuration with `actions: [\"allocate\"]` and `tiers`\n387: \n388: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler ClusterRole\n389: - **GIVEN** scheduler needs broad cluster permissions\n390: - **WHEN** ClusterRole is templated\n391: - **THEN** ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL have rules covering:\n392:   - `apiextensions.k8s.io/customresourcedefinitions`\n393:   - `\"\"` (core): `events, pods, pods/status, pods/binding, persistentvolumeclaims, persistentvolumes, namespaces, services, replicationcontrollers, resourcequotas, nodes, configmaps`\n394:   - `storage.k8s.io`: storage-related resources\n395:   - `policy/poddisruptionbudgets`\n396:   - `scheduling.k8s.io/priorityclasses`\n397:   - `scheduling.volcano.sh/podgroups`\n398:   - `apps`: daemonsets, replicasets, statefulsets\n399:   - `coordination.k8s.io/leases`\n400:   - `resource.k8s.io`: resource claims\n401:   - `shard.volcano.sh/nodeshards`\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler Deployment\n404: - **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n405: - **WHEN** Deployment is templated\n406: - **THEN** Deployment `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL have:\n407:   - `replicas: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.replicas }}`\n408:   - `image` from volcano.scheduler.image values\n409:   - `args` including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`\n410:   - `securityContext` for container\n411:   - `volumes` for config and emptyDir\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler Service\n414: - **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n415: - **WHEN** Service is templated\n416: - **THEN** Service `volcano-agent-scheduler-service` SHALL have:\n417:   - `port: 8080`\n418:   - `annotations` for metrics\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ### Requirement: _helpers.tpl named templates\n423: \n424: The system SHALL provide helper templates for consistent naming and labeling across all resources.\n425: \n426: #### Scenario: Name helper template\n427: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` is created\n428: - **WHEN** `{{ template \"agentcube.name\" . }}` is invoked\n429: - **THEN** it SHALL return `.Chart.Name` or nameOverride\n430: \n431: #### Scenario: Fullname helper template\n432: - **GIVEN** helpers tpl defines fullname\n433: - **WHEN** `{{ template \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}` is invoked\n434: - **THEN** it SHALL return fully qualified resource name using release name + chart name + overrides\n435: \n436: #### Scenario: Labels helper template\n437: - **GIVEN** helpers tpl defines labels\n438: - **WHEN** `{{ include \"agentcube.labels\" . }}` is invoked\n439: - **THEN** it SHALL return standard labels:\n440:   - `app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ template \"agentcube.name\" . }}`\n441:   - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n442:   - `app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}`\n443:   - `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}`\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Image helper template\n446: - **GIVEN** helpers tpl defines image helper\n447: - **WHEN** image path needs construction\n448: - **THEN** helper SHALL combine repository and tag with proper format\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ### Requirement: CRD files in crds/ directory\n453: \n454: The system SHALL ship CRD definitions that are installed before templates.\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: CRD directory location\n457: - **GIVEN** CRDs need to be bundled\n458: - **WHEN** chart is packaged\n459: - **THEN** CRDs SHALL be in `manifests/charts/base/crds/` directory\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD\n462: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` exists\n463: - **WHEN** CRD is installed\n464: - **THEN** CRD SHALL define:\n465:   - `metadata.name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n466:   - `group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n467:   - `versions: v1alpha1` (served + storage)\n468:   - `scope: Namespaced`\n469:   - `spec.required: maxSessionDuration, podTemplate, sessionTimeout, targetPort`\n470:   - `spec.maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`)\n471:   - `spec.sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`)\n472:   - `spec.targetPort` (array of port objects)\n473:   - `spec.podTemplate` (full PodSpec-shaped schema)\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD\n476: - **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` exists\n477: - **WHEN** CRD is installed\n478: - **THEN** CRD SHALL define:\n479:   - `metadata.name: codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n480:   - `group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n481:   - `versions: v1alpha1`\n482:   - `scope: Namespaced`\n483:   - `spec.authMode` (enum `picod|none`, default `picod`)\n484:   - `spec.maxSessionDuration` (default `8h`)\n485:   - `spec.sessionTimeout` (default `15m`)\n486:   - `spec.template` (required: image, command, args, env, resources)\n487:   - `spec.warmPoolSize` (optional int32)\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ### Requirement: Helm lint and template validation\n492: \n493: The system SHALL pass Helm lint and produce valid rendered templates.\n494: \n495: #### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n496: - **GIVEN** chart is complete\n497: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n498: - **THEN** lint SHALL pass with no errors\n499: \n500: #### Scenario: Template rendering produces valid YAML\n501: - **GIVEN** chart templates are complete\n502: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base` is executed\n503: - **THEN** output SHALL be valid Kubernetes YAML for all enabled components\n504: \n505: #### Scenario: Template rendering with values override\n506: - **GIVEN** custom values are provided\n507: - **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base -f custom-values.yaml` is executed\n508: - **THEN** output SHALL reflect custom values correctly\n509: \n510: ---\n511: \n512: ### Requirement: E2E deployment integration\n513: \n514: The system SHALL support E2E test deployment via helm upgrade --install.\n515: \n516: #### Scenario: E2E Helm install command\n517: - **GIVEN** E2E test environment (Kind cluster)\n518: - **WHEN** `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` deploys AgentCube\n519: - **THEN** command SHALL be:\n520:   ```bash\n521:   helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n522:     --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n523:     --create-namespace \\\n524:     --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n525:     --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n526:     --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n527:     --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n528:     --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[...]' \\\n529:     --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n530:     --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n531:     --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n532:     --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n533:     --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[...]' \\\n534:     --wait\n535:   ```\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: E2E local image references\n538: - **GIVEN** images are built and loaded into Kind\n539: - **WHEN** helm install runs\n540: - **THEN** image repository SHALL reference local image names (e.g., `workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`) without registry prefix\n541: \n542: ---\n543: \n544: ## Constants Summary\n545: \n546: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n547: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n548: | `DEFAULT_PORT` | `8080` | `values.yaml` | Default HTTP port for services |\n549: | `REDIS_PORT` | `6379` | `values.yaml` | Default Redis port |\n550: | `DEFAULT_REPLICAS` | `1` | `values.yaml` | Default replica count |\n551: | `DEFAULT_CPU_LIMIT` | `500m` | `values.yaml` | Default CPU limit |\n552: | `DEFAULT_MEMORY_LIMIT` | `512Mi` | `values.yaml` | Default memory limit |\n553: | `DEFAULT_CPU_REQUEST` | `100m` | `values.yaml` | Default CPU request |\n554: | `DEFAULT_MEMORY_REQUEST` | `128Mi` | `values.yaml` | Default memory request |\n555: | `DEFAULT_IMAGE_PULL_POLICY` | `IfNotPresent` | `values.yaml` | Default pull policy |\n556: | `DEFAULT_SESSION_TIMEOUT` | `15m` | CRDs | Default session timeout |\n557: | `DEFAULT_MAX_SESSION_DURATION` | `8h` | CRDs | Default max session duration |\n558: \n559: ---\n560: \n561: ## Dependencies Summary\n562: \n563: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n564: |---------|---------|---------|\n565: | `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template rendering and release management |\n566: | `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | API versions for Deployment, Service, RBAC, CRD resources |\n567: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `main` | Sandbox CRDs from sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox |\n568: | `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD generation from Go types |\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## File Changes Summary\n573: \n574: | File | Action | Description |\n575: |------|--------|-------------|\n576: | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Added | Helm Chart metadata |\n577: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Added | Default configuration values |\n578: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Added | Named template helpers |\n579: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Added | WorkloadManager Deployment + Service |\n580: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Added | Router Deployment + Service |\n581: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Added | WorkloadManager RBAC resources |\n582: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Added | Router RBAC (conditional) |\n583: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Added | Volcano scheduler (conditional) |\n584: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | Added | AgentRuntime CRD definition |\n585: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | Added | CodeInterpreter CRD definition |\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## References\n590: \n591: - proposal.md — AR-030 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n592: - deployment/design.md — Reference implementation details\n593: - ci-cd/design.md — E2E Helm usage patterns\n594: - sandbox-orchestration/design.md — Component configuration details\n595: - Helm 3 Documentation — Chart structure, templates, values best practices\n596: - Kubernetes API Reference — Deployment, Service, RBAC schemas\n597: \n598: ---\n599: \n600: ## Validation Checklist\n601: \n602: - [ ] `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes with no errors\n603: - [ ] `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base` produces valid YAML\n604: - [ ] WorkloadManager Deployment renders with correct image, env, probes\n605: - [ ] WorkloadManager Service renders with correct port and selector\n606: - [ ] Router Deployment renders with Redis and WorkloadManager URLs in env\n607: - [ ] Router Service renders with correct port mapping\n608: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has all required RBAC rules\n609: - [ ] Router RBAC renders conditionally when `router.rbac.create=true`\n610: - [ ] Volcano scheduler renders conditionally when `volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n611: - [ ] `_helpers.tpl` provides name, fullname, labels templates\n612: - [ ] CRD files are valid and match controller-gen output\n613: - [ ] E2E script can deploy with `helm upgrade --install`\n614: - [ ] Custom values override defaults correctly\n\n(End of file - total 614 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Helm Chart metadata file with correct API version and component information.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775884441960,"end":1775884441969}}}}
